			"value":"<p class=\"flavour\"><i>A shard of nothingness holds fast any creature that slips too close.</i></p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>At-Will âœ¦ Augmentable, Conjuration, Force, Implement, Psionic</b></p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Standard Action</b><b> &#8226; </b><b>Ranged</b> 10</p><p><b>Effect:</b> You conjure a void shard in an unoccupied square within range. Any creature that starts its turn adjacent to the shard is slowed until the end of its turn. At the start of your next turn, the shard disappears and you use the Void Shard Attack power. </p><p><b>Augment 1 </b> </p><p><b>Effect:</b> As above, and when the void shard is conjured, it uses the Void Shard Attack power as a free action, with the range Close burst 3. </p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Target:</b> Each enemy in the burst </p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Attack:</b> Intelligence vs. Reflex </p><p><b>Hit:</b> The void shard pulls the target 3 squares. </p><p>Published in Psionic Power, page(s) 93. </p>",
